CatDescriptText: Joseph D. Brown, unemployed, East Liberty was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 19, 1960, pg. C1 with question "Why do you think Negroes voted so heavily for Senator John F. Kennedy, Democrat, for President, in last Tuesday's election?" Answer reads: "I think a lot of Negroes remembered the depression under President Hoover, and how well things progressed under President Roosevelt and the Democrats. And Kennedy, they believe, will do the same as Roosevelt."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Joseph D. Brown wearing trench coat and plaid button down collared shirt, standing against telephone pole, with buildings in background
